Expval_Merge_Runner.py usage

Run all stages with the default project paths:

```powershell
python Expval_Merge_Runner.py run-all `
  --expval-root "F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\s_empty\expvals" `
  --lnpdb-root "F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\s_empty\target" `
  --lnpdb-root "F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\Source_head_tail_separated_f" `
  --lnpdb-root "F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\Source_DOI_added_f" `
  --output-root "F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\expval_merge_outputs"
```
python Expval_Merge_Runner.py run-all `
  --expval-root "F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\s_empty\expvals" `
  --lnpdb-root "F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\s_empty\target" `
  --output-root "F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\s_empty\expval_merge_outputs"

Run all stages using the manifest defaults:

```powershell
python Expval_Merge_Runner.py run-all --config expval_merge_workspace\merge_manifest.json
```

Run stages one by one:

```powershell
python Expval_Merge_Runner.py observe --config expval_merge_workspace\merge_manifest.json
python Expval_Merge_Runner.py build-key-map --config expval_merge_workspace\merge_manifest.json
python Expval_Merge_Runner.py normalize-expvals --config expval_merge_workspace\merge_manifest.json
python Expval_Merge_Runner.py normalize-lnpdb --config expval_merge_workspace\merge_manifest.json
python Expval_Merge_Runner.py build-candidates --config expval_merge_workspace\merge_manifest.json
python Expval_Merge_Runner.py merge --config expval_merge_workspace\merge_manifest.json --mode fill_existing
python Expval_Merge_Runner.py validate --config expval_merge_workspace\merge_manifest.json
```

Useful output files:

```text
F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\expval_merge_outputs\merged_lnpdb_like.csv
F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\expval_merge_outputs\merge_conflicts.csv
F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\expval_merge_outputs\merge_review_flags.csv
F:\내 드라이브\LNPDB_update_1\expval_merge_outputs\merge_qc_report.json
```

Notes:

- Original input files are not modified.
- Figure/Table classification uses the currently logged-in Codex CLI by default; `OPENAI_API_KEY` is not required.
- Check CLI authentication with `codex login status`; run `codex login` once if it reports `Not logged in`.
- `partition_inventory.csv` and `partitioned\...` show the figure/table split used before matching.
- Only `experimental_value` is filled.
- Rows with non-empty `experimental_value` are not overwritten.
- Use `--mode fill_existing` for conservative filling.
- Use `--mode long_expand` only when one LNPDB-like row should expand into multiple group/condition rows.
